cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a method for improving person re-identification using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces an ensemble method for CNNs, which suggests that it could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper focuses on improving performance on benchmark datasets, which could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
